nal entirely). Thus, there exist origins in which\nthe ECD model fits the data with high confidence but incorrect estimated\nlocation of the primary current segment. In such cases, the dipole is fit to a\nsegment of the volume current. If one were unaware of any origin translations,\nsuch ECD fits may be incorrectly interpreted as the primary current source.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Apr 2023 23:30:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-25"}
